&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.wilsonelser.com/&quot;&gt;Wilson Elser&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/strong&gt; we are redefining what it means to work at a national law firm. With more than 1,400 attorneys across 46 offices nationwide, we are recognized among the top 100 law firms by &lt;em&gt;The American Lawyer&lt;/em&gt; and ranked #36 in the &lt;em&gt;National Law Journal’s&lt;/em&gt; survey of the nation’s largest law firms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our continued success is built on a culture of collaboration, innovation, client service, and mutual respect. We are committed to fostering an environment where employees are empowered to grow their careers, contribute meaningfully, and thrive professionally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Wilson Elser is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Attorney Sourcing Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; to join our national Talent Acquisition team. This role will focus on identifying, engaging, and developing pipelines of attorney talent across the firm’s practice areas and geographic markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;This is a remote or hybrid position that may be based in any state where Wilson Elser has an office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;The Attorney Sourcing Specialist will play a key role in supporting the firm’s attorney recruiting efforts by proactively identifying and engaging qualified lateral attorney candidates. This position will focus heavily on sourcing, market research, direct outreach, and pipeline development for associate, senior associate, Of Counsel, and partner-level attorney openings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;The ideal candidate will be an experienced legal recruiter with strong sourcing skills, knowledge of the lateral attorney market, and the ability to effectively communicate with attorneys about career opportunities. This person should be highly proactive, organized, persuasive, and comfortable developing creative sourcing strategies in a competitive recruiting environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively source lateral attorney candidates for openings across the firm’s offices, practice groups, and client teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute targeted sourcing strategies using LinkedIn Recruiter, legal directories, Leopard Solutions/SurePoint, law firm websites, bar association resources, industry publications, referrals, networking, and other research tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market mapping to identify attorneys with relevant practice area experience, geographic alignment, client experience, and potential long-term fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain pipelines of qualified attorney candidates for current and future hiring needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and send tailored outreach messages to prospective candidates and manage follow-up communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct initial candidate outreach and introductory conversations to assess interest, experience, compensation expectations, practice alignment, and potential fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with attorney recruiters, Talent Acquisition leadership, hiring partners, and practice group leaders to understand hiring priorities and candidate profiles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide market intelligence regarding candidate availability, compensation expectations, competitor hiring activity, and sourcing challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and timely candidate records, sourcing activity, and pipeline updates in the applicant tracking system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track sourcing metrics, outreach effectiveness, response

